## Security Best Practices Implemented

### 1. Input Validation
- Validate query parameters for type and range
- Set limits on input sizes to prevent denial of service
- Use whitelisting for acceptable inputs

### 2. Error Handling
- Wrap routes in try-catch blocks
- Implement a global error handler middleware
- Handle uncaught exceptions and rejections
- Avoid exposing stack traces in production

### 3. Security Headers
- X-Content-Type-Options prevents MIME type sniffing
- X-Frame-Options prevents clickjacking
- X-XSS-Protection enables XSS filtering
- Strict-Transport-Security enforces HTTPS
- Content-Security-Policy mitigates XSS attacks

